inline_comments.message:
This is an example of the old quote: "if you can't fix it, feature it". In this case, you try to send a message via 'Util.deliver', it fails, and you declare victory!

I think it would be better to fix it -- my original comment was as follows:

        // throws an exception:
        //     java.lang.IllegalStateException: Policy Engine is stopped
        // if policy engine is started, it still throws an exception:
        //     java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: no reverse coder has been found
        //assertTrue(Util.deliver("testTopic", "test"));

I now realize what is needed -- in addition to starting the Policy Engine, I believe you need to create at least one controller, which includes the following properties:

noop.sink.topics=testTopic
noop.sink.topics.testTopic.events=java.lang.String

It's also possible that you can just add the following 'props.put' (I'm not sure about this):

prop.put("noop.sink.topics.testTopic.events", "java.lang.String");
